  - Weighing evidence: the presence of large trace.self.error_rate and very large trace.self.duration_p95 on frontend-0, together with the largest frontend log.error_count spike, indicates that frontend-0 exhibits the earliest/strongest application-level failure symptoms at 18:29. The simultaneous node I/O spikes suggest host-level stress concurrent with frontend problems, but the clearest, highest-magnitude service-level signals point at frontend-0 as the most likely pod-level root (frontend-0 shows the largest trace and log deviations).
  - Conclusion: at 18:29 the strongest signal of failure is at the frontend layer (frontend-0 strongest), supported by but not fully explained by node I/O anomalies — i.e., frontends (particularly frontend-0) are the primary suspects; node I/O issues may be contributing or co-occurring.

